Tell them to get out of here.

51
00:09:33,086 --> 00:09:34,986
What are you standing there for?

52
00:09:47,300 --> 00:09:49,598
You watch your ass, all right?

53
00:09:59,045 --> 00:10:02,071
(TV playing)

54
00:10:02,148 --> 00:10:04,673
- You got everything you need?
- Yeah.

55
00:10:08,955 --> 00:10:13,289
- Hank: Be careful walking around.
- Yeah, yeah.

56
00:10:14,661 --> 00:10:17,789
(TV playing)

57
00:10:28,741 --> 00:10:30,504
Man:
You see these two boys here?

58
00:10:31,945 --> 00:10:33,503
They're my sons.

59
00:10:34,714 --> 00:10:36,409
They were on my property.

60
00:10:36,482 --> 00:10:39,918
No need to be scared of no little boys.
They ain't come to hurt you.

61
00:10:39,986 --> 00:10:43,080
No need to be letting off no shotgun
to tell them to leave, either.

62
00:10:44,290 --> 00:10:45,222
You understand?

63
00:10:46,492 --> 00:10:48,323
Then keep 'em off my property.

64
00:10:49,929 --> 00:10:53,194
They're friends to your son, okay?
He invited them here.

65
00:10:53,266 --> 00:10:55,359
They ain't trespassing,
they ain't hurting nobody.

66
00:10:56,436 --> 00:11:00,668
Man: Next time you wanna play cowboy,
I'm over here all the time.

67
00:11:02,141 --> 00:11:03,802
Well, you keep them
off my property.

68
00:11:03,876 --> 00:11:06,276
- I think you heard me, sir.
- I think you heard me too.

69
00:11:06,346 --> 00:11:07,438
All right?

70
00:11:08,881 --> 00:11:10,314
Come on boys, let's go.

71
00:11:27,700 --> 00:11:29,668
Aw, shit!

72
00:11:33,206 --> 00:11:35,401
- You're all right, Dappa.
- Yeah, I'm all right.

73
00:11:35,475 --> 00:11:37,534
- You're sure?
- Yeah. It was loose.

74
00:11:37,610 --> 00:11:38,634
Yeah.

75
00:11:40,613 --> 00:11:43,514
Did you see what you did, Sonny?

76
00:11:43,583 --> 00:11:45,949
Yeah, I'm sorry.
It was my mistake.

77
00:11:46,019 --> 00:11:48,920
- Yeah, it was.
- It won't happen next time.

78
00:11:50,123 --> 00:11:51,988
Let's just keep going
till we get it right.

79
00:11:59,065 --> 00:12:02,125
(laughter)

80
00:12:02,201 --> 00:12:03,634
That's none of your business.

81
00:12:03,703 --> 00:12:05,603
- (more laughter)
- Woman: Woo!

82
00:12:05,671 --> 00:12:08,640
I'm surprised you're
talking like that to me.

83
00:12:08,708 --> 00:12:11,973
- You being a woman, you know?
- I'm a liberated woman.

84
00:12:12,045 --> 00:12:13,239
Better watch out,
Georgia Ann,

85
00:12:13,312 --> 00:12:15,473
Tommy's gonna sue you
for sexual harassment.

86
00:12:15,548 --> 00:12:16,708
Georgia Ann:
Oh, that's okay.

87
00:12:21,521 --> 00:12:23,045
Booter, how you doing?

88
00:12:24,724 --> 00:12:27,124
Just give me the $2.50, Sonny.

89
00:12:27,193 --> 00:12:28,421
I got it, Booter.

90
00:12:31,397 --> 00:12:34,855
- You keep the rest of it.
- Thanks, Mr. Grotowski.

91
00:12:37,036 --> 00:12:39,937
Hank: Just like I said,
no more mistakes, all right?

92
00:12:42,008 --> 00:12:45,808
I wanna make damn sure nobody
makes any mistakes, especially you.

93
00:12:48,848 --> 00:12:51,043
So when it gets time for us to do it...

94
00:12:52,318 --> 00:12:54,286
you can't mess up.

95
00:12:57,523 --> 00:13:00,253
That goes for me too,
and the rest of them.

96
00:13:02,728 --> 00:13:05,458
You ain't no different then us,
you can't screw it up.

97
00:13:07,300 --> 00:13:08,460
- (Dappa mumbles)
- Yeah.

98
00:13:08,534 --> 00:13:11,901
- That's Hank's boy.
- Georgia Ann: It's in the genes.

99
00:13:11,971 --> 00:13:13,233
Yeah, but he's a boy.

100
00:13:13,306 --> 00:13:16,969
- Yes, he is.
- He will be a man tomorrow.

101
00:13:17,043 --> 00:13:20,206
Man: In England, they give
the guy a party the night before.

102
00:13:21,547 --> 00:13:23,606
They call it the Monster's Ball.

103
00:13:28,521 --> 00:13:31,285
They don't want no lawyer, no preacher,
or anything like that around...

104
00:13:31,357 --> 00:13:33,154
So, it's just you and me.

105
00:13:36,729 --> 00:13:40,130
We can't think about what he did
or anything else about him.

106
00:13:40,199 --> 00:13:42,167
It's a job.
We have to do our job right.

107
00:14:29,182 --> 00:14:31,980
- (buzz)
- (gate opens)

108
00:14:37,323 --> 00:14:41,316
Man: I've been drawing a lot.
What about you?

109
00:14:41,394 --> 00:14:43,191
Boy: Yeah.

110
00:14:45,097 --> 00:14:49,193
Look here,
we ain't got a lot of time.

111
00:14:50,369 --> 00:14:52,269
I'm going to give you
all my drawings...

112
00:14:53,606 --> 00:14:55,801
all my clothes.

113
00:14:55,875 --> 00:14:57,240
When you get older,

114
00:14:58,477 --> 00:15:01,037
they may fit you and you may
want to wear them.

115
00:15:02,048 --> 00:15:04,414
I'm not gonna
see you again after this?

116
00:15:04,483 --> 00:15:06,144
No.

117
00:15:06,219 --> 00:15:07,584
Why?

118
00:15:10,056 --> 00:15:13,753
- 'Cause I'm a bad man.
- Who says?

119
00:15:13,826 --> 00:15:15,487
I do.

120
00:15:17,730 --> 00:15:19,823
But I want you to know something.

121
00:15:19,899 --> 00:15:21,332
What?

122
00:15:22,735 --> 00:15:24,066
You ain't me.

123
00:15:24,136 --> 00:15:27,902
- Yes I am.
- No, you're not.

124
00:15:29,375 --> 00:15:32,503
You're everything
that's good about me.

125
00:15:32,578 --> 00:15:36,480
You're the best of what I am,
that's what you are.

126
00:15:36,549 --> 00:15:40,144
This man you see sitting
here today, you ain't.

127
00:15:46,125 --> 00:15:49,151
Hey, baby.
You look nice, today.

128
00:15:49,228 --> 00:15:51,162
You always look nice.

129
00:15:53,733 --> 00:15:56,827
Tyrell, did you tell your daddy
what you won at school?

130
00:15:56,902 --> 00:15:58,335
Oh yeah, right.

131
00:15:58,404 --> 00:16:02,067
My drawing's getting used
for the school magazine cover.

132
00:16:02,141 --> 00:16:04,109
- You know what I did?
- What did you do?

133
00:16:04,176 --> 00:16:08,203
Go on, just tell him.
Don't be playing no guessing games.

134
00:16:08,281 --> 00:16:09,748
Tyrell:
I made a picture of you...

135
00:16:09,815 --> 00:16:11,749
sitting alone...

136
00:16:11,817 --> 00:16:13,546
in jail.

137
00:16:17,423 --> 00:16:19,254
The theme was solitude.

138
00:16:21,260 --> 00:16:24,957
Way to go, Ty. Way to go.
Put it there, boy.

139
00:16:26,365 --> 00:16:28,094
Not too bad.

140
00:16:37,576 --> 00:16:39,601
What's going on with the car?

141
00:16:41,447 --> 00:16:44,280
It's leaking radiator fluid.

142
00:16:44,350 --> 00:16:48,480
Take it in right away.
Have them check the hoses.

143
00:16:48,554 --> 00:16:51,182
The car get too hot,
you're gonna be in trouble.

144
00:16:58,164 --> 00:16:59,358
The house?

145
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:02,467
I'm losing it.

146
00:17:02,535 --> 00:17:05,436
I can't afford to make
the payments no more.

147
00:17:07,440 --> 00:17:08,873
Not no more.

148
00:17:10,376 --> 00:17:12,276
Man: I'm sorry, baby.

149
00:17:18,784 --> 00:17:21,412
Ty, let me and your mama
talk for a second.

150
00:17:21,487 --> 00:17:22,545
Okay.

151
00:17:30,830 --> 00:17:32,320
Man: Come on, now.

152
00:17:34,934 --> 00:17:38,233
Only reason I'm here,
so you can say goodbye to your son.

153
00:17:39,872 --> 00:17:40,998
Okay.

154
00:17:41,073 --> 00:17:44,941
I been coming here
for damn near 11 years, Lawrence.

155
00:17:46,312 --> 00:17:48,678
And I'm tired.

156
00:17:48,748 --> 00:17:50,739
I'm tired of coming here.

157
00:17:52,284 --> 00:17:55,117
- Officer #1: Time.
- So soon?

158
00:18:01,594 --> 00:18:03,653
I got to get going, baby.

159
00:18:16,876 --> 00:18:18,901
Time for me to go, Ty.

160
00:18:18,978 --> 00:18:22,379
I'm gonna call you.
You wait by the phone, okay?

161
00:18:22,448 --> 00:18:26,441
Come on now.
You got to let go.

162
00:18:26,519 --> 00:18:28,111
Woman:
Come on, Tyrell.

163
00:18:32,191 --> 00:18:36,355
For every time
I hurt you, I'm sorry.

164
00:18:36,429 --> 00:18:37,487
Officer #1: Come on.

165
00:18:39,665 --> 00:18:42,099
Officer #2: Ma'am, let's go.

166
00:18:42,168 --> 00:18:43,567
Let's go.

167
00:18:45,070 --> 00:18:46,401
Officer #2: Ma'am, let's go.

168
00:18:46,472 --> 00:18:49,566
- (door closes)
- I know my way out of here.

169
00:18:49,642 --> 00:18:50,768
Come on.

170
00:19:03,756 --> 00:19:07,055
Hank: He don't have
any outstanding appeal, so...

171
00:19:07,126 --> 00:19:09,594
looks like we're definitely
gonna do it tonight.

172
00:19:11,197 --> 00:19:12,562
Everybody okay?

173
00:19:12,631 --> 00:19:15,099
- You all right, Georgia Ann?
- I'm okay.

174
00:19:17,570 --> 00:19:19,333
Hank:
Dappa, is that hood ready?

175
00:19:19,405 --> 00:19:21,600
Yeah, it's fixed
and ready to go.

176
00:19:21,674 --> 00:19:22,732
All right.

177
00:19:24,043 --> 00:19:26,170
Anybody got anything to say?

178
00:19:26,245 --> 00:19:27,269
Hank: Tommy?

179
00:19:27,346 --> 00:19:31,407
Tommy: He likes to draw.
It calms him down.

180
00:19:31,484 --> 00:19:32,849
Draw?

181
00:19:32,918 --> 00:19:34,442
- Yeah.
- Okay.

182
00:19:34,520 --> 00:19:38,183
Phil, will you make sure he's got
whatever it is he needs to draw with?

183
00:19:38,257 --> 00:19:38,780
Yes, sir.

184
00:19:40,960 --> 00:19:43,121
Hank: Tommy, why don't you
lead us in prayer?

185
00:19:43,195 --> 00:19:44,184
Okay.

186
00:19:50,236 --> 00:19:53,433
- Guard: Open cell 1 3!
- (buzz)

187
00:19:56,876 --> 00:19:58,639
I'm here for your stuff, man.

188
00:19:58,711 --> 00:20:02,545
Tommy: ...that the Lord
save us his anointing.

189
00:20:02,615 --> 00:20:06,483
Ye will hear Him
in His holy Heaven,

190
00:20:06,552 --> 00:20:08,816
and the saving strength
of His right hand.

191
00:20:12,558 --> 00:20:14,651
Be careful with this.

192
00:20:14,727 --> 00:20:16,456
Don't worry about it, man.

193
00:20:16,529 --> 00:20:19,498
- Close 1 3!
- (buzz)

194
00:20:21,233 --> 00:20:23,201
Worry's all I've got.

195
00:20:23,269 --> 00:20:26,261
...some in chariots,
some in horses.

196
00:20:26,338 --> 00:20:28,966
but we remember
the name of the Lord, our God.

197
00:20:30,309 --> 00:20:34,939
They're brought down and fallen,
but we are risen and stand upright.

198
00:20:35,014 --> 00:20:38,381
Save us, Lord. Let the King
hear us when we call Him.

199
00:20:38,450 --> 00:20:40,941
TV host:
Sky surfing is when you skydive,

200
00:20:41,020 --> 00:20:44,478
with a board attached to your feet,
and try to do different maneuvers.

201
00:20:44,557 --> 00:20:48,584
A camera flyer flies
with a camera on top of a helmet,

202
00:20:48,661 --> 00:20:49,821
filming the sky surfer...

203
00:20:49,895 --> 00:20:53,160
and flies with the sky surfer
for capturing the moves.

204
00:20:53,232 --> 00:20:55,632
My camera flyer is my husband,
Craig O'Brien.

205
00:21:00,406 --> 00:21:02,374
Sonny: I'm gonna put
these on nice and loose.

206
00:21:03,876 --> 00:21:05,468
Everything's gonna
be okay, right?

207
00:21:05,544 --> 00:21:06,909
Yes, sir.

208
00:21:13,552 --> 00:21:15,213
What about my last phone call?

209
00:21:16,789 --> 00:21:18,654
Warden says it's a bad idea.

210
00:21:21,126 --> 00:21:22,354
Turn around.

211
00:21:27,766 --> 00:21:30,360
Maybe you could call my son
and tell him that I tried.

212
00:21:32,071 --> 00:21:33,436
I don't think so.

213
00:21:34,607 --> 00:21:35,631
Sonny: Okay.

214
00:21:38,777 --> 00:21:41,439
- Open 1 3.
- (buzz)

215
00:21:53,892 --> 00:21:56,360
TV host: Our freefall
is usually around 60 seconds,

216
00:21:56,428 --> 00:22:00,296
and the normal altitude
we jump from is 1 2,500 feet.

217
00:22:01,533 --> 00:22:02,761
Let's go.

218
00:22:07,406 --> 00:22:09,874
- Hank: Close 1 3.
- (buzz)

219
00:22:17,516 --> 00:22:21,816
TV ad: Starting to feel a little
cramped by your present surroundings?

220
00:22:21,887 --> 00:22:24,617
Maybe it's time
to expand your horizons.

221
00:22:24,690 --> 00:22:26,954
Maybe it's time
to think about ReMax.

222
00:22:27,026 --> 00:22:30,325
ReMax Associates
lead the real estate industry--

223
00:22:30,396 --> 00:22:32,057
I'm going to be right back.
Stay right there.

224
00:22:33,565 --> 00:22:36,762
TV ad: ReMax can help you find
a new home that meets all your needs,

225
00:22:36,835 --> 00:22:38,029
while selling your current house

226
00:22:38,103 --> 00:22:41,129
to someone who will find it
absolutely perfect.

227
00:22:41,206 --> 00:22:43,834
If you're looking for results,
look for ReMax.

228
00:22:43,909 --> 00:22:45,809
Nobody sells more real estate.

229
00:22:47,112 --> 00:22:48,670
(beep)

230
00:22:50,282 --> 00:22:51,943
(buzz)

231
00:23:09,735 --> 00:23:12,067
Lawrence:
Where's my paper and pencil?

232
00:23:12,137 --> 00:23:15,334
It's my right to have
my paper and pencil.

233
00:23:15,407 --> 00:23:16,431
Hank: I know.

234
00:23:16,508 --> 00:23:18,635
Your paper and pencil's
on the way.

235
00:23:18,711 --> 00:23:20,975
I promise you it is.

236
00:23:24,883 --> 00:23:26,373
(TV playing)

237
00:23:27,953 --> 00:23:29,614
(keys clicking)

238
00:24:02,354 --> 00:24:03,685
Thank you.

239
00:24:06,258 --> 00:24:07,691
You're welcome.

240
00:25:09,087 --> 00:25:11,282
Here you go, Lawrence.

241
00:25:14,993 --> 00:25:16,756
Is that done?

242
00:25:20,566 --> 00:25:22,693
Sonny: Let's see.

243
00:25:24,369 --> 00:25:27,031
Wow.
That's nice.

244
00:25:27,105 --> 00:25:28,970
It's real nice.

245
00:25:30,442 --> 00:25:32,501
I don't look
this good in person.

246
00:25:33,846 --> 00:25:36,610
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

247
00:25:38,116 --> 00:25:40,311
You're welcome.

248
00:25:46,525 --> 00:25:48,618
You all right?

249
00:25:48,694 --> 00:25:50,889
Sonny.

250
00:25:50,963 --> 00:25:54,797
- Just breathe.
- Hank: Sonny.

251
00:25:57,970 --> 00:25:59,164
Sonny, sit down.

252
00:26:01,206 --> 00:26:03,936
I said, sit down.
Sit down.

253
00:26:12,918 --> 00:26:15,716
Come on, Lawrence.
Come on, buddy.

254
