509
00:57:15,712 --> 00:57:17,942
I don't really know her.

510
00:57:19,850 --> 00:57:22,876
- I'll take her home.
- That's a good idea.

511
00:57:22,953 --> 00:57:24,215
Hank: Yeah,
I'll take her home.

512
00:57:32,696 --> 00:57:35,187
Could you do me a favor
and throw that away for me?

513
00:57:35,265 --> 00:57:37,665
- Yes, sir.
- I'd appreciate that.

514
00:57:54,618 --> 00:57:56,552
Hank:
Where do you live?

515
00:57:59,356 --> 00:58:02,291
Ma'am, you'll have to tell me
where you live.

516
00:58:04,628 --> 00:58:06,755
Now, I'll go
in your purse.

517
00:58:06,830 --> 00:58:08,991
I'm letting you know
I'm going in your purse

518
00:58:09,065 --> 00:58:11,033
to find
an address on you.

519
00:58:49,873 --> 00:58:52,137
You should call
some of your kin people

520
00:58:52,209 --> 00:58:54,006
or a friend or something.

521
00:59:02,352 --> 00:59:05,082
I'm going to have to go.

522
00:59:05,155 --> 00:59:06,918
You gonna be all right?

523
00:59:08,458 --> 00:59:12,485
They told me to call
the Coroner's Office in the morning.

524
00:59:14,097 --> 00:59:15,962
I'm sorry?

525
00:59:16,032 --> 00:59:19,331
They told me to call
the Coroner's Office.

526
00:59:19,402 --> 00:59:22,235
They said
they gonna do an autopsy.

527
00:59:23,506 --> 00:59:26,805
I don't know why
they'll do an autopsy.

528
00:59:27,978 --> 00:59:30,105
He was hit by a car.

529
00:59:35,785 --> 00:59:38,686
I imagine that'll help them
find out who did it.

530
00:59:40,190 --> 00:59:42,715
You really believe
they'll do that?

531
00:59:43,793 --> 00:59:46,421
I believe
they'll try their best.

532
00:59:47,497 --> 00:59:50,159
He's a Black kid.

533
00:59:50,233 --> 00:59:52,428
You think
they'll do that?

534
01:00:00,911 --> 01:00:04,244
Here's your bag.
I'll leave it on the floor.

535
01:00:11,221 --> 01:00:13,451
I'm real sorry.

536
01:01:01,671 --> 01:01:03,298
Mr. Grotowski?

537
01:01:03,373 --> 01:01:05,807
Just want to say
sorry about Sonny.

538
01:01:05,875 --> 01:01:10,141
- We liked him a lot.
- We feel bad, sir.

539
01:01:14,184 --> 01:01:16,550
Which one of you is Willie
and which's one's Harry?

540
01:01:16,619 --> 01:01:18,985
He's Willie.

541
01:01:19,055 --> 01:01:20,852
He's Darryl.

542
01:01:23,059 --> 01:01:25,892
I'll see ya.
I appreciate that.

543
01:01:40,410 --> 01:01:44,244
I'm going over to the cafe.
Do you want a ride?

544
01:01:46,116 --> 01:01:48,516
You sure
you don't mind?

545
01:01:48,585 --> 01:01:50,849
I'm going
that way anyway.

546
01:01:52,822 --> 01:01:55,484
(country music playing)

547
01:02:04,901 --> 01:02:06,994
Is this music
all right with you?

548
01:02:08,905 --> 01:02:12,397
- 'Cause I can change it.
- No, it's cool.

549
01:02:14,444 --> 01:02:16,912
You ain't got a car?

550
01:02:16,980 --> 01:02:19,244
It's broke.

551
01:02:19,315 --> 01:02:21,408
I'm saving
to get me another one.

552
01:02:33,363 --> 01:02:36,560
Leticia:
$8.64. Thank you.

553
01:02:36,633 --> 01:02:38,794
Hank: Thank you.

554
01:02:38,868 --> 01:02:41,393
You have
a good shift, okay?

555
01:02:41,471 --> 01:02:43,302
Leticia: Thanks.

556
01:02:46,543 --> 01:02:48,511
- Leticia: Thank you.
- You're welcome.

557
01:03:19,409 --> 01:03:21,673
Hey, Pop?

558
01:03:21,744 --> 01:03:24,941
- Look it here.
- What are those for?

559
01:03:25,014 --> 01:03:27,744
I bought a gas station.

560
01:03:29,119 --> 01:03:31,849
- That right?
- Mmm-hmm.

561
01:03:34,457 --> 01:03:36,448
It's all bought and paid for.

562
01:03:36,526 --> 01:03:38,289
- We own it.
- (Buck sneezes)

563
01:03:40,830 --> 01:03:44,425
Don't say ''we.''
You own it.

564
01:03:45,969 --> 01:03:47,834
I didn't buy it.

565
01:03:49,339 --> 01:03:54,641
- Yeah, well...
- I wouldn't have bought no gas station.

566
01:03:54,711 --> 01:03:56,838
Is that right?

567
01:04:00,150 --> 01:04:02,983
I would have stuck
to what I knew best.

568
01:04:03,052 --> 01:04:07,045
- What's that?
- Corrections Officer.

569
01:04:08,558 --> 01:04:10,583
Right.

570
01:04:10,660 --> 01:04:13,060
Well, I ain't
a Corrections Officer no more.

571
01:04:13,129 --> 01:04:15,222
I'm a gas-station owner.

572
01:04:16,499 --> 01:04:19,491
I already made the deal.
It's too late, Pop.

573
01:04:19,569 --> 01:04:21,764
You want me
to fix you something?

574
01:04:21,838 --> 01:04:23,328
No.

575
01:04:28,878 --> 01:04:30,072
Hey.

576
01:04:49,933 --> 01:04:51,525
Here you go.

577
01:04:53,803 --> 01:04:55,430
How are you doing?

578
01:04:56,506 --> 01:05:00,442
I'm doing all right.
Tired.

579
01:05:00,510 --> 01:05:03,707
- You gonna eat something?
- Chocolate ice cream.

580
01:05:03,780 --> 01:05:06,510
Plastic spoon.

581
01:05:08,218 --> 01:05:09,879
You got it.

582
01:05:13,690 --> 01:05:15,317
Thank you.

583
01:05:18,595 --> 01:05:21,428
- You're all set?
- Mmm-hmm.

584
01:05:22,498 --> 01:05:25,592
- About time for you to get off?
- Mmm-hmm.

585
01:05:26,970 --> 01:05:29,370
Did you want me
to give you a ride?

586
01:05:30,640 --> 01:05:31,971
No...

587
01:05:32,041 --> 01:05:34,305
I really couldn't ask you
to do that.

588
01:05:34,377 --> 01:05:36,641
It's right on the way home.

589
01:05:41,918 --> 01:05:46,048
- You sure you don't mind?
- No, I'd be happy to.

590
01:05:46,122 --> 01:05:48,022
Okay.

591
01:05:50,326 --> 01:05:53,784
- Hank: It's right on Prospect Street.
- Leticia: Clement's?

592
01:05:53,863 --> 01:05:56,229
- Yeah, Clement's.
- You bought Clement's?

593
01:05:56,299 --> 01:05:57,823
Yeah.

594
01:05:57,900 --> 01:05:59,868
Leticia:
I know Clement.

595
01:05:59,936 --> 01:06:04,168
- I can't stand that man.
- He ain't going to be running it.

596
01:06:04,240 --> 01:06:06,333
Leticia:
Well, that's good.

597
01:06:06,409 --> 01:06:08,877
Thanks for the ride.

598
01:06:08,945 --> 01:06:11,209
Can I ask you
a question?

599
01:06:15,385 --> 01:06:17,512
Why did you help me?

600
01:06:19,355 --> 01:06:23,189
- What do you mean?
- When you took us to the hospital.

601
01:06:23,259 --> 01:06:25,193
Why did you do that?

602
01:06:31,534 --> 01:06:34,059
I don't know. I guess--

603
01:06:34,137 --> 01:06:35,798
I just--

604
01:06:38,408 --> 01:06:41,502
doing the right thing,
I guess.

605
01:06:49,419 --> 01:06:51,580
My son died.

606
01:06:54,724 --> 01:06:56,453
And--

607
01:06:59,495 --> 01:07:01,622
well, he--

608
01:07:01,698 --> 01:07:03,791
he died and then--

609
01:07:06,836 --> 01:07:09,771
I never was
a very good father.

610
01:07:15,878 --> 01:07:17,869
He was a good kid.

611
01:07:22,352 --> 01:07:24,980
I guess that somehow
I just--

612
01:07:27,490 --> 01:07:30,584
when I see what you're going
through there

613
01:07:30,660 --> 01:07:34,994
it made me think about something.
I don't know.

614
01:07:37,233 --> 01:07:39,997
You know when you feel
like you can't breathe?

615
01:07:49,812 --> 01:07:53,475
And you can't
get out to--

616
01:07:56,219 --> 01:07:58,210
from inside yourself,
you know?

617
01:07:58,287 --> 01:07:59,777
Really.

618
01:08:08,264 --> 01:08:10,255
Do you want
to come inside?

619
01:08:14,804 --> 01:08:17,170
I like these curtains.

620
01:08:20,643 --> 01:08:23,669
I got these here curtains
on credit.

621
01:08:23,746 --> 01:08:28,046
I never heard of anybody
getting curtains on credit before.

622
01:08:30,720 --> 01:08:33,746
What do you think?
Ain't they cute?

623
01:08:33,823 --> 01:08:36,690
I love these curtains.

624
01:08:36,759 --> 01:08:39,193
Hank: They're good
and red all right.

625
01:08:39,262 --> 01:08:41,355
I got--

626
01:08:41,431 --> 01:08:46,130
I got these curtains right here
on credit.

627
01:08:46,202 --> 01:08:49,171
And the man told me...

628
01:08:49,238 --> 01:08:52,002
that I wasn't supposed
to get this deal.

629
01:08:52,074 --> 01:08:53,769
But I think
he liked me,

630
01:08:53,843 --> 01:08:57,210
and he told me I could have
these curtains on credit.

631
01:08:57,280 --> 01:08:59,214
I said,
what the hell?

632
01:08:59,282 --> 01:09:01,512
Red curtains
will be great for my place.

633
01:09:01,584 --> 01:09:03,449
So I said,
I'll take it.

634
01:09:03,519 --> 01:09:07,319
- So I got me some red curtains.
- Damn straight.

635
01:09:09,992 --> 01:09:12,483
You sure suck
that whiskey down.

636
01:09:12,562 --> 01:09:15,497
I mean,
Lord have mercy.

637
01:09:17,967 --> 01:09:24,099
My husband used to love him
some Jack Daniel's.

638
01:09:25,675 --> 01:09:28,508
Like I said,
it's a good drink.

639
01:09:32,548 --> 01:09:35,949
- Wait. I'll show you something.
- Okay.

640
01:09:38,054 --> 01:09:39,919
Sit right here.

641
01:09:48,898 --> 01:09:52,834
What you got?
Some kind of a school annual?

642
01:09:52,902 --> 01:09:54,426
No.

643
01:09:54,504 --> 01:09:56,301
These pictures
right here--

644
01:09:59,242 --> 01:10:02,700
these are my husband's
drawings right here.

645
01:10:05,081 --> 01:10:06,309
Lawrence.

646
01:10:06,382 --> 01:10:09,749
My husband,
he drew those.

647
01:10:14,590 --> 01:10:18,993
He got himself electrocuted
over there in Jackson.

648
01:10:20,796 --> 01:10:22,957
He got himself--

649
01:10:26,802 --> 01:10:30,636
These right here,
these are my son Tyrell's.

650
01:10:33,910 --> 01:10:36,174
He drew these.

651
01:10:36,245 --> 01:10:38,440
He drew all of these
right here.

652
01:10:42,685 --> 01:10:46,086
He got his talent
from the old man, I guess.

653
01:10:46,155 --> 01:10:47,520
Didn't he?

654
01:10:47,590 --> 01:10:50,320
That's the only thing
that negro ever gave that boy,

655
01:10:50,393 --> 01:10:52,293
was some drawing.

656
01:10:52,361 --> 01:10:54,329
Taught him
how to draw.

657
01:10:54,397 --> 01:10:57,560
It runs in the family,
sounds like it.

658
01:10:57,633 --> 01:10:59,260
You know...

659
01:11:02,271 --> 01:11:04,330
he was a good kid.

660
01:11:04,407 --> 01:11:06,568
He was
a really good kid.

661
01:11:06,642 --> 01:11:08,769
He was so good.

662
01:11:08,844 --> 01:11:10,402
He was--

663
01:11:10,479 --> 01:11:13,175
he really--
he loved me.

664
01:11:13,249 --> 01:11:15,513
He really loved me.

665
01:11:15,585 --> 01:11:17,314
I understand.

666
01:11:20,289 --> 01:11:22,780
He was so fat.

667
01:11:24,026 --> 01:11:26,256
You saw how fat he was.

668
01:11:28,631 --> 01:11:30,997
I don't care what
I brought in this house,

669
01:11:31,067 --> 01:11:32,694
he just ate it up!

670
01:11:32,768 --> 01:11:34,395
I don't care
what it was I brought in.

671
01:11:34,470 --> 01:11:36,438
I bring
some Popeye's chicken,

672
01:11:36,505 --> 01:11:40,168
that boy eat the whole thing
before I can get a bite!

673
01:11:40,242 --> 01:11:43,871
He would eat
his ass off!

674
01:11:44,947 --> 01:11:48,383
You haven't seen
nobody eat like--

675
01:11:50,219 --> 01:11:53,814
He would eat candy
and gumballs.

676
01:11:53,889 --> 01:11:57,017
He'd make me take him
to the Super K-Mart

677
01:11:57,093 --> 01:12:00,585
and he put them quarters
in that gumball machine.

678
01:12:00,663 --> 01:12:03,359
He had to wait
till he get the red gumball.

679
01:12:04,500 --> 01:12:07,128
He always had to get
the red gumball.

680
01:12:09,472 --> 01:12:12,236
He sounds like a character,
I guess.

681
01:12:14,710 --> 01:12:16,575
He'd get
that red gumball

682
01:12:16,646 --> 01:12:19,581
and he'd just eat
on that red gumball.

683
01:12:26,589 --> 01:12:27,920
Hey.

684
01:12:29,458 --> 01:12:31,358
I was a good mother.

685
01:12:31,427 --> 01:12:36,262
I did-- every single thing
I can think to do--

686
01:12:36,332 --> 01:12:39,267
I was really good.
I was really good.

687
01:12:39,335 --> 01:12:42,498
- I was a good mother.
- I understand.

688
01:12:44,140 --> 01:12:46,165
I didn't want him
to be fat like that.

689
01:12:46,242 --> 01:12:48,642
I did not want my baby
to be fat like that,

690
01:12:48,711 --> 01:12:50,975
'cause I know,
a Black man in America,

691
01:12:51,047 --> 01:12:53,538
you can't be like that!
And I tried to--

692
01:12:55,451 --> 01:12:57,544
I was trying
to tell him,

693
01:12:57,620 --> 01:13:00,282
''You can't be like that,

694
01:13:00,356 --> 01:13:02,381
you can't be like that
in America, and a Black man.''

695
01:13:02,458 --> 01:13:04,221
I was just...

696
01:13:06,962 --> 01:13:10,557
I'm not sure
what you want me to do.

697
01:13:11,634 --> 01:13:14,102
I want--

698
01:13:14,170 --> 01:13:16,866
I want you
to make me feel better.

699
01:13:16,939 --> 01:13:19,840
I want you
to make me feel better.

700
01:13:20,910 --> 01:13:24,243
I want you
to make me feel good.

701
01:13:25,881 --> 01:13:28,008
I want you
to make me feel good.

702
01:13:28,084 --> 01:13:30,314
Can you make me
feel good?

703
01:13:30,386 --> 01:13:32,684
Can you make me
feel good?

704
01:13:32,755 --> 01:13:34,985
Can you make me
feel good?

705
01:13:36,092 --> 01:13:38,356
Make me feel good.

706
01:13:40,963 --> 01:13:43,329
I don't know
what to feel good's about.

707
01:13:43,399 --> 01:13:47,597
Just make me feel good!
Just make me feel good!

708
01:14:35,317 --> 01:14:37,785
(Leticia wails)

709
01:15:17,726 --> 01:15:19,455
(wailing)

710
01:15:27,336 --> 01:15:29,566
(Hank grunts)

711
01:16:10,212 --> 01:16:12,646
I felt it too.

712
01:16:14,650 --> 01:16:16,379
I needed you.

713
01:16:16,452 --> 01:16:18,784
I needed you so much.

714
01:16:20,990 --> 01:16:23,424
I needed you so much.

715
01:16:24,927 --> 01:16:27,794
I hadn't felt anything
in so long.

716
01:16:32,001 --> 01:16:33,628
Leticia: Thank you.

717
01:17:17,046 --> 01:17:19,378
(retching)

718
01:17:30,192 --> 01:17:31,955
You okay?

719
01:17:36,365 --> 01:17:39,698
Me getting sick doesn't have
anything to do with you.

720
01:17:52,381 --> 01:17:54,315
Pop?

721
01:17:57,453 --> 01:17:59,250
Hey, Pop?

722
01:18:00,322 --> 01:18:03,291
Buck:
I'm in the damn bathroom!

723
01:18:07,029 --> 01:18:08,826
Hank: What the hell
happened to you?

724
01:18:08,897 --> 01:18:11,866
I twisted my ankle
trying to take a bath.

725
01:18:12,935 --> 01:18:16,234
Damn it,
I told you to be careful.

726
01:18:19,908 --> 01:18:21,739
Buck: Goddamn!

727
01:18:23,212 --> 01:18:25,009
Hank:
Wiggle your toes.

728
01:18:29,818 --> 01:18:31,308
- You feel that?
- Yeah.

729
01:18:31,387 --> 01:18:33,116
Yeah?

730
01:18:36,492 --> 01:18:38,653
I'm sinking.

731
01:18:38,727 --> 01:18:42,288
- What are you talking about?
- I ain't worth shit.

732
01:18:44,666 --> 01:18:47,829
- You stop that.
- I can't clean myself.

733
01:18:47,903 --> 01:18:51,202
Can't walk to the kitchen
without falling.

734
01:18:51,273 --> 01:18:55,107
Can't get to the phone
before it stops ringing.

735
01:18:56,278 --> 01:18:59,372
I don't feel
like a man anymore.

736
01:19:01,383 --> 01:19:03,374
You're a man, Pop.

737
01:19:04,453 --> 01:19:08,116
Can't even remember
what a woman smells like.

738
01:19:13,295 --> 01:19:15,456
(hammering in background)

739
01:19:33,649 --> 01:19:35,844
Girl:
There's a man here.

740
01:19:35,918 --> 01:19:37,215
Man: Where?

741
01:19:40,122 --> 01:19:41,521
Man: Thank you.

742
01:19:44,193 --> 01:19:47,185
- How are you doing?
- Hey, how are you doing?

743
01:19:47,262 --> 01:19:48,820
All right.

744
01:19:50,432 --> 01:19:53,060
What can I do for you?

745
01:19:53,135 --> 01:19:57,037
I got this '89 Comanche
out there...

746
01:19:58,273 --> 01:20:00,673
it needs a lube job,
new points and plugs.

747
01:20:00,742 --> 01:20:03,040
I was wondering
if you'd work on it for me.

748
01:20:04,446 --> 01:20:07,381
Yeah.
When do you need it by?

749
01:20:07,449 --> 01:20:09,781
Just as quick
as you can, really.

750
01:20:11,086 --> 01:20:12,610
Maggie!

751
01:20:12,688 --> 01:20:15,054
Leave that alone, baby.
Put that down.

752
01:20:19,595 --> 01:20:22,860
I can get that to you
about tomorrow afternoon,

753
01:20:22,931 --> 01:20:24,489
late tomorrow then?

754
01:20:25,567 --> 01:20:27,432
I'd appreciate it.

755
01:20:28,937 --> 01:20:33,169
Maybe them boys of yours can--
if they're not doing anything--

756
01:20:33,242 --> 01:20:35,836
wash it and wax it
and everything?

757
01:20:35,911 --> 01:20:37,538
I'm selling it.

758
01:20:37,613 --> 01:20:38,807
All right.

759
01:20:40,349 --> 01:20:42,579
I'll ask them.
I'll tell them about it.

760
01:20:42,651 --> 01:20:44,448
I'm sure
they wouldn't mind.

761
01:20:47,022 --> 01:20:49,217
I can't take this.

762
01:20:51,560 --> 01:20:53,323
It was my son's.

763
01:20:53,395 --> 01:20:57,832
It'd mean a lot to him.
He'd want somebody to use it.

764
01:20:57,900 --> 01:21:00,198
I ain't saying
I don't want it.

765
01:21:01,570 --> 01:21:04,198
I just can't take it.

766
01:21:04,273 --> 01:21:06,434
I want you to have it.
I really do.

767
01:21:06,508 --> 01:21:08,373
It'd mean a lot to me.

768
01:21:13,882 --> 01:21:16,407
Let's just take it
for a little spin.

769
01:21:19,454 --> 01:21:20,512
Come on.

770
01:21:23,292 --> 01:21:27,956
- I ain't even got my shoes on.
- We won't go far. Let's go.

771
01:21:31,400 --> 01:21:33,391
You see how it drives.

772
01:21:43,445 --> 01:21:46,972
- What the hell is this?
- Stick shift.

773
01:22:16,144 --> 01:22:19,113
Hank:
Here's the insurance and title,

774
01:22:19,181 --> 01:22:21,411
and all the papers you need.
It's all set.

775
01:22:21,483 --> 01:22:25,544
- Okay.
- I'd like to see you tonight.

776
01:22:25,621 --> 01:22:30,183
- We should do that.
- Is that all right?

777
01:22:37,065 --> 01:22:39,932
- I'll see you later.
- See you.

778
01:25:07,416 --> 01:25:09,111
Hank?

779
01:25:11,119 --> 01:25:12,484
Hank: That's good.

780
01:25:12,554 --> 01:25:14,613
Hello?

781
01:25:15,724 --> 01:25:16,656
Hank!

782
01:25:19,428 --> 01:25:21,692
It's Leticia.

783
01:25:27,235 --> 01:25:29,226
I'm coming on in,
Hank.

784
01:25:36,278 --> 01:25:37,973
Hank?

785
01:25:39,114 --> 01:25:40,945
Buck:
Who are you?

786
01:25:43,718 --> 01:25:47,017
You just walked
in my house?

787
01:25:47,088 --> 01:25:48,612
My bad.

788
01:25:48,690 --> 01:25:51,591
- I--
- Hank?

789
01:25:51,660 --> 01:25:54,959
- You're looking for Hank?
- Yes.

790
01:25:55,030 --> 01:25:57,294
Is he here?

791
01:25:57,365 --> 01:25:59,128
Who are you?

792
01:26:00,268 --> 01:26:03,795
My name
is Leticia Musgrove.

793
01:26:03,872 --> 01:26:05,237
And...

794
01:26:05,307 --> 01:26:07,639
me and Hank is...

795
01:26:09,511 --> 01:26:11,206
friends.

796
01:26:12,280 --> 01:26:14,510
Musgrove?

797
01:26:18,553 --> 01:26:20,748
Please,
little darling...

798
01:26:21,990 --> 01:26:24,515
have you got
a cigarette?

799
01:26:24,593 --> 01:26:26,493
Yeah.

800
01:26:27,596 --> 01:26:30,759
But it look to me like
you don't need to be smoking.

801
01:26:35,270 --> 01:26:37,238
Come on.

802
01:26:37,305 --> 01:26:39,364
Have you got one?

803
01:26:55,123 --> 01:26:56,750
Match?

804
01:27:08,403 --> 01:27:12,362
So, is Hank here?

805
01:27:13,875 --> 01:27:16,673
Yeah.
He'll be back shortly.

806
01:27:16,745 --> 01:27:19,270
I'm Buck, his father.

807
01:27:21,449 --> 01:27:23,849
Is that for Hank?

808
01:27:23,919 --> 01:27:25,352
Yeah.

809
01:27:25,420 --> 01:27:27,081
It's a gift.

810
01:27:29,991 --> 01:27:32,357
I'll see he gets it.

811
01:27:43,171 --> 01:27:45,196
Buck: Woo!

812
01:27:47,943 --> 01:27:49,308
Damn!

813
01:27:54,983 --> 01:27:57,110
Hank must have done
something right

814
01:27:57,185 --> 01:27:59,653
to deserve
a fine hat like this.

815
01:28:02,123 --> 01:28:04,318
I guess he did.

816
01:28:04,392 --> 01:28:08,988
In my prime, I had a thing
for nigger juice myself.

817
01:28:10,699 --> 01:28:12,724
Hank's just
like his daddy.

818
01:28:13,802 --> 01:28:16,737
He ain't a man
till he split dark oak.

819
01:28:34,589 --> 01:28:37,786
Hey, Leticia?
Hang on.

820
01:28:37,859 --> 01:28:39,486
Where are you going?

821
01:28:39,561 --> 01:28:42,325
Hey!
Where are you going?

822
01:28:42,397 --> 01:28:44,957
- What happened?
- I met your daddy.

823
01:28:45,033 --> 01:28:47,263
- Get off me!
- You can't do that.

824
01:28:47,335 --> 01:28:49,929
Give me a chance.
Whatever he did--

825
01:28:50,005 --> 01:28:52,030
It don't matter
a whole lot, do it?

826
01:28:52,107 --> 01:28:54,905
- Give me a chance to talk to you.
- Get off me!

827
01:29:13,928 --> 01:29:16,419
Buck:
We're family.

828
01:29:16,498 --> 01:29:19,331
I'm your father.
Remember that.

829
01:29:23,038 --> 01:29:24,403
Hank?

830
01:29:26,708 --> 01:29:29,142
What's your problem?

831
01:29:33,682 --> 01:29:36,845
- Hank: I believe that's it.
- Thank you.

832
01:29:37,919 --> 01:29:40,888
I didn't date
that thing at the bottom.

833
01:29:40,955 --> 01:29:42,445
No problem.

834
01:29:42,524 --> 01:29:45,220
Anything below that line,
I didn't do.

835
01:29:48,463 --> 01:29:52,263
Now, you will take
good care of him?

836
01:29:52,333 --> 01:29:55,825
- Woman: Oh, yes.
- Hank: 'Cause...

837
01:29:57,338 --> 01:29:59,898
I want him
to go out in peace.

838
01:30:00,975 --> 01:30:03,500
You must love him
very much.

839
01:30:06,514 --> 01:30:08,345
No, I don't.

840
01:30:09,417 --> 01:30:12,477
But he's my father.
So, there it is.

841
01:30:33,141 --> 01:30:36,440
They'll get you
a TV set tomorrow.

842
01:30:37,512 --> 01:30:40,003
Finally getting rid
of me, huh?

843
01:30:40,081 --> 01:30:42,811
They'll
take care of you.

844
01:30:42,884 --> 01:30:46,376
There's a telephone at the end
of the hall. You can call me.

845
01:30:46,454 --> 01:30:49,218
This is it.

846
01:30:49,290 --> 01:30:50,757
I guess so.

847
01:30:53,161 --> 01:30:54,822
I'm stuck.

848
01:30:56,898 --> 01:30:58,991
Me too.

849
01:31:01,469 --> 01:31:03,334
Buck: I don't want
to go out like this.

850
01:31:05,907 --> 01:31:07,772
Me neither.

851
01:31:12,347 --> 01:31:14,144
Goodbye, Pop.

852
01:32:11,506 --> 01:32:12,939
What?

853
01:32:15,743 --> 01:32:17,643
You want your car back?

854
01:32:17,712 --> 01:32:20,442
No, I don't
want the car back.

855
01:32:20,515 --> 01:32:22,483
I mean for you to keep that.

856
01:32:22,550 --> 01:32:24,211
What?

857
01:32:24,285 --> 01:32:27,254
I want you to know
I sent him away.

858
01:32:30,558 --> 01:32:32,856
I ain't got time to talk.

859
01:32:32,927 --> 01:32:35,725
I wish you would talk to me.

860
01:32:38,166 --> 01:32:40,157
Y'all ready to order?

861
01:33:13,334 --> 01:33:16,167
- Hank: How are you doing, Ryrus?
- All right. How are you?

862
01:33:16,237 --> 01:33:18,967
- I'm all right.
- Who's Leticia?

863
01:33:21,109 --> 01:33:23,100
My girlfriend.

864
01:33:27,282 --> 01:33:30,615
Sheriff's Department.
Hello?

865
01:33:43,965 --> 01:33:46,559
- Who's banging on my door?
- The Sheriff's Department.

866
01:33:46,634 --> 01:33:50,126
- Time to go, lady.
- No, no wait.

867
01:33:50,204 --> 01:33:52,069
- Time to go.
- No. Here.

868
01:33:52,140 --> 01:33:54,108
No, I don't take
anything.

869
01:33:54,175 --> 01:33:56,200
You settle with your landlord,
then I go away.

870
01:33:56,277 --> 01:33:57,767
No,
I got the money.

871
01:33:57,845 --> 01:33:59,745
I suggest
you get fully dressed.

872
01:33:59,814 --> 01:34:03,910
- I'm going to put you out.
- You ain't putting me out.

873
01:34:04,986 --> 01:34:07,682
I 'bout got the money.
I'm still saving--

874
01:35:13,955 --> 01:35:15,980
I painted
the ceiling and the wall

875
01:35:16,057 --> 01:35:18,651
and fixed it up
a little bit.

876
01:35:18,726 --> 01:35:20,956
I figured I ought to.

877
01:35:21,029 --> 01:35:23,827
I'll move your stuff here
so you don't have to worry with it.

878
01:35:27,635 --> 01:35:30,798
I'm going to the kitchen
to get a thing or two

879
01:35:30,872 --> 01:35:35,434
so if you want to relax,
make yourself comfortable.

880
01:35:35,510 --> 01:35:37,137
Whatever you want to do.

881
01:36:25,359 --> 01:36:29,193
- This is Tyrell's.
- I thought I'd put it up there.

882
01:36:29,263 --> 01:36:31,288
That's my boy's room.

883
01:36:33,701 --> 01:36:35,464
All right. Here.

884
01:36:37,105 --> 01:36:39,232
You can go up
if you want to.

885
01:36:45,580 --> 01:36:47,411
Can I look at these?

886
01:36:47,482 --> 01:36:49,416
Yeah, go ahead.

887
01:36:56,824 --> 01:36:58,849
That's him right there.

888
01:37:02,196 --> 01:37:04,061
He don't look like you.

889
01:37:05,666 --> 01:37:07,600
He got his mother in him.

890
01:37:21,516 --> 01:37:24,747
Hank: I don't mind sleeping
across the hall if you want me to.

891
01:37:24,819 --> 01:37:26,810
- Maybe you should sleep by yourself.
- No...

892
01:37:26,888 --> 01:37:29,152
I wouldn't feel good

893
01:37:29,223 --> 01:37:31,714
if you left me in here
all by myself.

894
01:37:32,793 --> 01:37:35,318
I just want you
to be comfortable here.

895
01:37:37,832 --> 01:37:40,562
I want you
to be comfortable too.

896
01:38:06,627 --> 01:38:08,822
Hank:
I want to take care of you.

897
01:38:10,298 --> 01:38:12,232
Leticia: Good.

898
01:38:12,300 --> 01:38:15,929
'Cause I really need
to be taken care of.

899
01:38:53,074 --> 01:38:55,634
Can I touch you?

900
01:39:00,114 --> 01:39:01,274
Yeah.

901
01:40:03,377 --> 01:40:05,811
Did you feel that?

902
01:40:07,615 --> 01:40:09,207
Oh yeah.

903
01:40:19,026 --> 01:40:21,051
Did it feel good?

904
01:40:25,933 --> 01:40:27,560
Yeah.

905
01:40:32,039 --> 01:40:34,507
I didn't hurt you
or anything?

906
01:40:36,510 --> 01:40:39,138
Not in a bad way.

907
01:40:55,296 --> 01:40:57,264
What?

908
01:40:59,433 --> 01:41:02,402
Nothing, I just--

909
01:41:05,406 --> 01:41:08,204
I want to go out
and buy some ice cream.

910
01:41:12,179 --> 01:41:14,204
- Now?
- Yeah.

911
01:41:16,917 --> 01:41:19,112
It just feels right.

912
01:41:24,925 --> 01:41:27,758
- Okay.
- Well...

913
01:41:30,531 --> 01:41:32,726
Can you buy me some?

914
01:41:32,800 --> 01:41:34,700
Yeah.

915
01:41:34,769 --> 01:41:36,930
What kind do you want?

916
01:41:39,073 --> 01:41:40,734
Chocolate.

917
01:44:48,562 --> 01:44:49,961
Hey.

918
01:44:51,065 --> 01:44:53,397
I bought
some chocolate ice cream.

919
01:44:56,403 --> 01:44:58,166
Are you okay?

920
01:45:01,542 --> 01:45:03,703
You sure?

921
01:45:09,783 --> 01:45:11,751
You look real pretty.

922
01:45:14,154 --> 01:45:16,213
Let's go out on the steps.
You want to?

923
01:45:17,825 --> 01:45:19,816
Let's go.

924
01:46:48,982 --> 01:46:52,383
I went by our station
on the way home.

925
01:46:52,453 --> 01:46:54,648
I like the sign.

926
01:47:11,238 --> 01:47:13,570
I think
we'll be all right.

